  "prompt": "How much does it cost to attend a TED talk?",
  "response": "Attending the main, annual TED Conference is notoriously expensive. In recent years, the cost of a ticket has been around **$10,000**.\n\nHowever, there are many other ways to experience TED content that are much more accessible:\n\n*   **TEDx Events:** These are independently organized events that follow the TED format. The pricing varies greatly depending on the location, organizers, and content, but they are typically far less expensive than the main TED Conference, ranging from free to a few hundred dollars.\n*   **TED.com:** The TED website offers a vast library of TED Talks available for free viewing.\n*   **TED Radio Hour:** A partnership with NPR that explores ideas from TED Talks.\n*   **TED Books:** Short books expanding on ideas presented at TED Conferences.\n*   **TED Courses:** Online learning programs offering in-depth explorations of various topics.\n\n",
